[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dundee police probe Baxter Park bowling pavilion blaze

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police are investigating after a deliberate fire at a bowling pavilion in Dundee.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Fire crews were called to Baxter Park at about 21:00 on Thursday after the old lawn bowls pavilion was set alight.
Firefighters wearing breathing apparatus used a hose reel jet to extinguish the flames. Dundee City Council is to assess the full extent of the damage to the building.
Officers are investigating and have appealed for information.
